article.headline: N. Iowa 59, Illinois St. 55
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- Northern Iowa got 17 points from Ali Farohkmanesh and three late free throws by Kwadzo Ahelegbe to beat Illinois State 59-55 Wednesday for its ninth straight victory. The Missouri Valley Conference-leading Panthers (15-6, 9-1) last won nine games in a row during the 1963-64 season when they were in Division II. Ahelegbe finished with 13 points. He had two clutch free throws after Illinois State (17-4, 6-4) closed within 56-55 on a 3-pointer by Champ Oguchi with 19 seconds left and added another free throw with one second to play. The game was tied for the last time at 46 with 7:30 remaining. The Panthers went up 53-48 and never trailed again. Oguchi had a team-high 11 points and Lloyd Phillips and Dinma Odiakosa added 10 each for the Redbirds.
